"Vitamins and minerals are micronutrients essential for hundreds of bodily functions including bone health, immune defense, energy production, and wound healing. There are 13 essential vitamins and numerous vital minerals. Deficiencies can lead to serious health problems — for example, vitamin D deficiency affects bone health, iron deficiency causes anemia, and vitamin C deficiency impairs immunity. Most needs can be met through a varied diet.",
